sub_title: Tourism Expert; MD and Founder Travel Counsellors Netherlands & Belgium
summary:
Fred has been running Travel Counsellors Netherlands since November 2005, prior to which he worked with the group for several months as a consultant. Within a few years he built a profitable, trend setting travel business from 4 franchisees to more than 200 and an annual turnover of € 65M. Fred founded Travel Counsellors Belgium and functions actively as its Managing Director. In March 2017 he also took on the responsibility for Travel Counsellors Australia as its Acting Managing Director until May 2018. 

He is also a TV Presenter and an active free lance Travel & Lifestyle writer and blogger for various  magazines .

Fred has held previously a number of senior roles in the international travel industry. Chief Executive Officer for the Qatar Tourism Authority and a member of the board for the Qatar National Hotels. 

Fred is a member of the advisory Board of the Dutch Stenden University for Professional Education and founder and chairman of the registered children's charity Helping Hands.
